---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Wargame Modules · Ray Weiss"
  description="Commissioned digital modules of print wargames: rules-enforced engines, real maps and counters, playable in a browser from a double-click. $400 to $800 by scope."
>
  <div
    slot="sheet-id"
    class="sheet-id"
    aria-label="Sheet identification"
  >
    <div class="plate">
      <span class="num">PL. I.C</span> Wargame Modules · Commissions Open
    </div>
    <div class="edition">Edition 2026.07 · Brooklyn, NY</div>
  </div>

  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
    <header class="hero">
      <img
        src="/counter-rw.svg"
        alt="Ray Weiss unit counter"
        class="counter"
        width="96"
        height="72"
      />
      <div>
        <h1>Wargame Modules</h1>
        <p class="dek">Print wargames. Running locally in a browser.</p>
        <div class="slug" aria-label="Identification">
          <span><strong>UNIT</strong> RW / 26</span>
          <span class="sep">/</span>
          <span><strong>TYPE</strong> Digital modules</span>
          <span class="sep">/</span>
          <span><strong>STATUS</strong> Open, selective</span>
          <span class="sep">/</span>
          <span><strong>SCALE</strong> $400 to monster</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="bio">
      <p>
        I build digital modules of print wargames on commission. The map, the counters, and the
        procedures are translated into a local engine. You unzip a folder and double-click
        index.html. It runs in your browser. No installs, no accounts, no internet connection
        required.
      </p>
    </div>

    <section aria-labelledby="module-includes">
      <div class="section-head">
        <h2 class="section-label" id="module-includes">
          <span class="pl">PL. I.C</span>What a module includes
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="prose-body mt-6">
        <p>
          Automated bookkeeping and chart lookups. Hotseat play with information masking for cards
          and hidden movement. Every roll logs the cited rule. Games save to local files.
          Programmed opponents available as an add-on where the system supports them.
        </p>
      </div>

      <figure class="mt-8">
        <img
          src="/images/wargame-modules/nab-crop.webp"
          alt="Napoleon at Bay digital module. Hex map of the Champagne countryside with marshal counters, and a turn control panel showing weather, morale, and the segment sequence."
          width="800"
          class="w-full rounded"
          loading="eager"
        />
        <figcaption class="mt-3 font-mono text-xs text-subtle">
          Napoleon at Bay. Turn control, weather, morale, and the segment sequence on the digitized
          map.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <figure class="mt-8">
        <img
          src="/images/wargame-modules/flattop-crop.webp"
          alt="Flattop digital module. Search-board hexes over the Solomons with an umpire traffic panel reporting air operations by teletype."
          width="800"
          class="w-full rounded"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <figcaption class="mt-3 font-mono text-xs text-subtle">
          Flattop. The umpire reports contacts by teletype. Hidden movement stays hidden.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <figure class="mt-8">
        <img
          src="/images/wargame-modules/pog-crop.webp"
          alt="Paths of Glory digital module. The Central Powers card hand beside the eastern map edge, each card offering operations or event play."
          width="800"
          class="w-full rounded"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <figcaption class="mt-3 font-mono text-xs text-subtle">
          Paths of Glory. The Central Powers hand, each card playable for ops or event through the
          engine.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="track-record" class="mt-16">
      <div class="section-head">
        <h2 class="section-label" id="track-record">
          <span class="pl">PL. I.C</span>Track record
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="prose-body mt-6">
        <p>
          Four modules built over five weeks. Napoleon at Bay, Flattop, Paths of Glory, For the
          People. A single client commissioned the set and ordered the second pair after testing
          the first. Card-driven engines pass six hundred automated rules checks before delivery.
          Playable previews arrive within two days of commission.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="demo" class="mt-16">
      <div class="section-head">
        <h2 class="section-label" id="demo">
          <span class="pl">PL. I.C</span>Try one
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="prose-body mt-6">
        <p>
          1914: East Prussia: The World Undone is my own published design through Conflict
          Simulations. The link below opens the public playtest build. It demonstrates the exact
          product class I deliver for commissions: a rules-enforced engine, hex map, counters, and
          hotseat play. Open it in your browser and play.
        </p>
      </div>
      <figure class="mt-8">
        <a href="https://twu-ep-pt-dba90a.pages.dev/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          <img
            src="/images/wargame-modules/twu-demo.webp"
            alt="1914: East Prussia: The World Undone in play. Full hex map of East Prussia with German and Russian counters, turn track, victory point track, and combat results table."
            width="800"
            class="w-full rounded"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </a>
        <figcaption class="mt-3 font-mono text-xs text-subtle">
          <a href="https://twu-ep-pt-dba90a.pages.dev/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            Play the East Prussia 1914 playtest &rarr;
          </a>
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="pricing" class="mt-16">
      <div class="section-head">
        <h2 class="section-label" id="pricing">
          <span class="pl">PL. I.C</span>Pricing
        </h2>
        <span class="section-count">04 tiers ——</span>
      </div>
      <ol class="infra-list">
        <li>
          <div class="infra-meta">
            <span><span class="k">Price</span><span class="v">$400</span></span>
            <span><span class="k">Scope</span><span class="v">Smaller games</span></span>
          </div>
          <span class="infra-title">Single map, limited counter mix</span>
          <p class="infra-desc">Chart-driven procedures. No card deck.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="infra-meta">
            <span><span class="k">Price</span><span class="v">$600</span></span>
            <span><span class="k">Scope</span><span class="v">Standard operational</span></span>
          </div>
          <span class="infra-title">Full map, card deck or comparable subsystems</span>
          <p class="infra-desc">The Napoleon at Bay and Flattop class.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="infra-meta">
            <span><span class="k">Price</span><span class="v">$800</span></span>
            <span><span class="k">Scope</span><span class="v">Large card-driven</span></span>
          </div>
          <span class="infra-title">Extensive decks, layered mechanics, multi-front</span>
          <p class="infra-desc">The Paths of Glory and For the People class.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="infra-meta">
            <span><span class="k">Price</span><span class="v">Quoted</span></span>
            <span><span class="k">Scope</span><span class="v">Monster games</span></span>
          </div>
          <span class="infra-title">Monster games quoted per project</span>
          <p class="infra-desc">Multiple maps, thousands of counters, campaign scale.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
      <div class="prose-body mt-6">
        <p>
          You pay half up front to reserve the build spot, half on completion. Thirty days of
          reasonable feature requests and bug fixes after delivery are included.
        </p>
        <p>
          These are private builds for owners of print copies. Publishers may commission licensed
          editions under separate terms.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="hex-rule" aria-hidden="true">
      <img src="/hex-ornament.svg" alt="" width="96" height="32" />
    </div>

    <aside class="featured" aria-labelledby="start">
      <span class="section-label" id="start">Start</span>
      <h3>One email starts it</h3>
      <p class="desc">
        Email <a href="mailto:rweiss@consimsltd.com">rweiss@consimsltd.com</a>. Provide the game
        title, edition, and any specific technical requirements. If the work fits, I reply with
        scope and price. If it does not, I say so.
      </p>
      <a href="mailto:rweiss@consimsltd.com" class="cta">Email me &rarr;</a>
    </aside>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
